SUBENT        A1230003   20260217   20260508   20260508       A133
BIB                 12         47
REACTION   (3-LI-6(P,INL)3-LI-6,PAR,DA)
SAMPLE     The 6Li targets used ranged in thickness from about
           30 to 130 ug/cm2. The lithium target thickness
           traversed by the beam was about 50 ug/cm2 in gamma-ray
           measurements.
METHOD     The measurements were made at different times with
           different targets, although the procedures followed
           were quite similar.
           (COINC) The normalization of the angular distribution
           was determined from an angular distribution obtained
           later at the same energy by the direct measurement
           technique, This distribution in turn was normalized
           to the 6Li,(p,el)6Li cross section.
DETECTOR   (NAICR) 5.08 by 5.08 cm and 7.62 by 7.62 cm.
           The gamma-rays were observed with a Harshaw 10.16-cm
           long by 10.16-cm diameter cylindrical Nal(T1) crystal
           mounted on a CBS 7819 photomultiplier tube.
           (SIBAR) Detector was used to monitor target thickness
           and beam integration.
MONITOR    (3-LI-6(P,EL)3-LI-6,,DA) One of the particle
           detectors used in the study of the 6Li(p,inl)6Li*
           reaction (see ref.) was used to monitor target
           thickness and beam integration. This was done by
           comparing the proton yield from the 6Li(p,el)6L1
           reaction with the previously determined cross
           section see ref.).
MONIT-REF  (C1003001,W.D.Harrison+,J,PR,132,2607,1963)
CORRECTION The energy scale given was corrected for target
           thickness.
FLAG       (1.) Measurement in coincidence
           (2.) Direct measurement
COMMENT    At 5.80 MeV the data from the coincidence
           measurements and from the direct measurements are
           given separately (see FLAG).
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) The greater part of the standard error given
           for each point was estimated from the statistics of
           the number of coincidences obtained, and the smaller
           part from uncertainty in the correction for
           random coincidences.
           (ERR-2) Error in the normalization relative to
           the correct 6Li(p,el)6Li cross section.
STATUS     (TABLE,,W.D.Harrison,T,HARRISON,1967) Table 5. Part of
           data presented on fig.2 of NP/A,92,260,1967
HISTORY    (20250831A) SD: SF9=EXP deleted from REACTION code.
           STATUS updated. COS-ERR -> COS-ERR-D; ERR-DIG added.
           (20260217A) SD: BIB updated. The digitized data were
           replaced with tabulated data from thesis.
ENDBIB              47
