BIB                  9         22
REACTION   (2-HE-4(HE3,P)3-LI-6,PAR,SIG,,D4PI)
SAMPLE     Gas target 4He. The gas pressure was 8 cm of mercury.
           Tantalum was used for the target tube in order to
           reduce background radiation produced by particles
           striking its walls.
INC-SOURCE  Negatively charged 3He ions
DETECTOR   (NAICR) 7.62 by 7.62 cm.
PART-DET   (G)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-2) The standard error given for each point was
           estimated from a combined statistical and background
           error.
           (ERR-1) The total normalization standard error.
           (ERR-3) Error due to gain shift and uncertainty in
           pressure measurement and in beam integration.
MISC-COL   (MISC) 7Be center-of-momentum energy.
STATUS     (TABLE,,W.D.Harrison,T,HARRISON,1967) Table 7. Same
           data presented on fig.3 of NP/A,92,260,1967
